questions.answer:
Implement IAM tag-based access control combined with an S3 bucket policy to enforce per-tenant isolation. Assign each tenant a unique tenant-id tag to their IAM role, then use IAM policies that grant Get/Put/List permissions only when the principal's aws:PrincipalTag/tenant-id matches the requested s3:prefix (tenant-id/*). The S3 bucket policy provides an additional enforcement layer, validating that access is restricted to the tenant's own prefix. A separate admin role with broader permissions can access all prefixes for auditing purposes.

**Tenant Role IAM Policy:**
```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "AllowTenantPrefixAccess",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": ["s3:GetObject", "s3:PutObject", "s3:ListBucket"],
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:s3:::corp-assets",
        "arn:aws:s3:::corp-assets/${aws:PrincipalTag/tenant-id}/*"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

**S3 Bucket Policy (Enforcement Layer):**
```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "EnforceTenantPrefixIsolation",
      "Effect": "Deny",
      "Principal": "*",
      "Action": "s3:*",
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:s3:::corp-assets",
        "arn:aws:s3:::corp-assets/*"
      ],
      "Condition": {
        "StringNotLike": {
          "s3:prefix": "${aws:PrincipalTag/tenant-id}/*"
        },
        "ArnNotEquals": {
          "aws:PrincipalARN": "arn:aws:iam::*:role/AdminRole"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

**Basic Test Plan:**
1. **Positive Test:** Tenant A (tenant-id=alpha) attempts read/write to corp-assets/alpha/* — Expected: Success
2. **Negative Test:** Tenant A attempts read/write to corp-assets/beta/* — Expected: Access Denied
3. **Admin Test:** Admin role attempts read on corp-assets/gamma/* — Expected: Success
4. **Validation:** Verify CloudTrail logs confirm correct Allow/Deny decisions for each scenario.

